<TITLE> BSF kills 1 at Meherpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Meherpur, Jan 16 (bdnews24.com)  India's Border Security Force (BSF) on Saturday handed over the body of a Bangladeshi citizen killed at the Kazipur border in Meherpur district. Alfaz Uddin, BDR sergeant of Kazipur camp said Indian border guards of Churutia camp in India's Nadia district shot dead Shahidul Islam when he crossed the border to retrieve cattle on Friday night. The body was handed over to Bangladesh Rifles at a flag meeting at 5:30pm on Saturday. Osman Gani, sub inspector of Gangni Police Station said that the body would be handed over to Shahidul's family after autopsy. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina at a press conference on Saturday, following her just-concluded tour to India, said Dhaka requested New Delhi during her Jan 10-13 visit to "take initiatives to stop killing BDR personnel and innocent Bangladeshi citizens on the borders". bdnews
